"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022919","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-12-19","<p>The current area of Victoria Tower Gardens is 18,848m<sup>2</sup> . The Memorial will take up 1387m<sup>2 </sup>which is approximately 7 per cent of the park; the remaining area will be publicly accessible.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2018-12-19T13:06:10.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022919/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022919/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-12-10","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is the current area of the Victoria Tower Gardens; what area will be taken up by the Holocaust Memorial and associated works; and what area will remain for recreational use.","false","Biography information for Lord Turnbull",,"Lord Turnbull","HL12171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022920","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-20","<p>The Department has made no assessment itself. However, Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs deals with complaints about underpayment of the National Minimum Wage and National Living Wage. It has worked with other agencies and departments to raise awareness of the rules and has undertaken targeted enforcement to ensure that workers are paid what they are legally owed.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-12-20T15:44:50.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022920/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022920/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-12-10","Home Care Services: Living Wage","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord O'Shaughnessy on 22 November (HL11744), what assessment they have made of whether local authorities are complying with guidelines to ensure that home care workers are paid the national living wage for travelling between appointments.","false","Biography information for Lord Wills",,"Lord Wills","HL12172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022921","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-13","<p>Interserve is an organisation identified by the Cabinet Office as a Strategic Supplier to the Government and as such is closely monitored by them via the Crown Representative who provides regular reports on their Financial Status to the Department of Health and Social Care. Currently these reports indicate that Departments should continue to trade with them as normal and should this situation change then Departments will be notified of any action required.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2018-12-13T12:02:44.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022921/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022921/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-12-10","Department of Health and Social Care: Interserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to monitor the financial health of Interserve.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","200580"
