"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022924","Women and Equalities","false","2018-12-13","<p>The Government believes that political parties have the prime responsibility for supporting their disabled candidates. We are undertaking a programme of work with disability stakeholders to help political parties to better support disabled candidates.</p><p>Alongside this work we have launched the EnAble Fund for Elected Office which is a £250,000 interim fund to support disabled candidates, primarily for the forthcoming local elections in May 2019.</p><p>The fund will help cover disability-related expenses people might face when seeking elected office which could include items such as British Sign Language Interpreters, Assistive Technology or taxi fares where other modes of transport are not appropriate.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-12-13T17:47:07.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022924/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022924/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-12-10","Candidates: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, with reference to the launch of the EnAble Fund for Elected Office, what support her Department is providing to help disabled candidates standing for parliamentary elections.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","200689"
