"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022996","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-12-13","<p>As the regulator of charities in England and Wales, the Charity Commission performs an important service on behalf of the public.</p><p> </p><p>The Commission has set out a new strategic direction and outlined what it believes is necessary to meet its purpose of ensuring charity can thrive and inspire trust so people can improve lives and strengthen society.</p><p> </p><p>In January 2018, government awarded the Charity Commission an additional £5 million a year and, in the Civil Society Strategy, committed to work with the Commission to ensure it is placed on a secure and sustainable financial footing and adequately resourced to meet future challenges.</p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2018-12-13T16:32:41.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022996/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022996/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-12-10","Charity Commission: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent assessment he has made of the future funding needs of the Charity Commission; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","200707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022997","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-12-13","<p>The Arts Council England (ACE) invests substantially in supporting the music education landscape. The Arts Council’s £75m investment in music education hubs reflects the government’s belief that all students should have access to an excellent, well-rounded education which includes the arts and music. ACE has also recently provided funding to Leeds College of Music for a festival of cutting edge music, sound art and visual installations; and the Royal Northern College of Music for the 2018 RNCM Brass Band Festival.</p><p> </p><p>In particular, ACE supports the orchestral sector’s engagement with conservatoires by working with Conservatoires UK to encourage collaboration between conservatories and the ACE National Youth Music Organisations, National Portfolio Organisations and Music Education Hubs.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-12-13T12:49:02.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022997/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022997/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-12-10","Music: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent support he has given to music conservatoires.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","200591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022998","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-12-17","<p>The data concerning the number of youth service centres that have closed down in Lambeth in each month since 2010 is not held by my department.</p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2018-12-17T16:52:24.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022998/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1022998/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-12-10","Youth Services: Lambeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many youth service centres have closed down in Lambeth in each month since 2010.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Chuka Umunna","200636"
